#warning-env(title: [Single-Anchoring Risk and Methodological Limitations])[
- The meta-analysis is a preprint (not peer-reviewed)
- The meta-analysis partially overlaps with DecodeME samples (not fully independent replication)
- The MVP cohort is ~90% male vs ME/CFS patient population ~75% female, potentially biasing results, masking female-specific risk variants, and producing tissue enrichment patterns that differ from a sex-matched cohort
- Organ-based enrichment methods have known annotation biases (GTEx brain samples have more sub-regions than peripheral tissues)
]
